content: Really 3.5 stars. App is above average but has too many quarks to be very good or great. Best feature is the wide variety of data export options. However, the time calculations are wrong. Eg. 3 hrs available over 5 days; assigning a task with 15 hrs of work gives an end time of 15 hrs & 45 minutes. A nonstandard week where M to F 3 hrs per day & Sat & Sun with 5 hrs each end times are wrong. The inability to designate a fix number of hrs p/d for a task for the length of the proj is a biglimit

I am still impressed by this app. I still used it almost 5 years later after downloading it. The two things I would add, if I could, is to be able to move noncompleted items, all in a group, and add dates to linked items. I tried moving an entire set of noncompleted items and the program also moved the completed ones. Still a fantastic program.

HARD IS GOOD I've noticed that apps that take only 5mins to learn run out of puff and get deleted. This app takes some learning. I've also noticed that as I keep banging away at it, my projects run better too. It's a maze worth figuring out..:-)
Works well. Wish it had a calander view
Good and honest üëç
Excellent App ,thank u
I've used it for years. It's scheduling features are unique nor have I found any competitive products in this price range. I use MS Project for work and this for personal.

Very useful app. But input methods, especially the date should be a lot more flexible so that a change in starting date/ time will automatically adjust subsequent dates and times accordingly in a project schedule.
Good job

Project Schedule is an easy to use project management tool. Starting with limited experience, I have been very quickly able to learn its functions and develop complex, multi-disciplinary programs. Exceptional value for money!
good app. would be great if resource management could be done from task list.
Brilliant app
simple to start using and plenty of options.

Minus to 3 stars. Not able to upload as mpp file even if i have purchased the app. Not able to select custom notification date. Notification shall be alerted before end date as well. Some summary task are 0% even after all sub tasks are 100%. Some summary task are 100% when only one of 2 subtask is 100%.
easy to use , great for tracking multiple projects. everything is right at your fingertips. A great tool to have! highly recommend
Haven't used for years, takes a bit getting used to it again. Once I remembered it became easier to use the only thing is adding resources to my tasks; how is it done?
like this app. very user friendly. i wish it had a way to send invites or alerts to those involved in each task to be able to schedule them.

My specific need for a project schedule app on mobile devise is one that allows me to plan my project on ms project & sync with Google calendar & tasks. Project schedule allows me to import my project and monitor closely on my mobile devise .
A great App to keep you more organized

App needs to mature. Has some good functionality but lacks controls. Can also use a user manual. It would be better if it could schedule projects from end dates and estimate start. Also having the ability to output multiple projects on the same spreadsheet would be very useful.
Once you learn how to use it and if you are adept at project management this app is a great mobile tool which performs lose to Microsoft project.

This is the best Project app I've come across.  Its got plenty of features to keep the average user busy.  Its great to have a usable app that I can lay a project plan out and manage it easily from my phone, and even save it to the cloud.  I find it more useful than other apps I've come across because I can add notifications to segments of my project with speech and customise sounds to played as alerts.  I can even define tasks in measurements of hours and minutes providing greater flexibility when planning a project.  The scheduling part of the app is a real bonus once you get your head around it.
If this had an online interface for quicker entry it'd be perfect
Too difficult to use and crashes a lot of times
Very handy!!!

I like the pro features & the ability to sync between the app and Google Tasks, but you can't sync between the app and Google Calendar. Nor can you sync projects between tablet and phone, which is a pain. So I use this app for project planning on my tablet, and still depend on June to sync tasks. Please consider syncing Calendars, not just tasks.
Very Comprehensive!
Sweet

What i was looking for. Great for scheduling and planning. Autozoom is one of the best for touchscreen UI. In auto mode it seeks the main task and scales to fit screen so all subtasks can be seen. So all i need is scroll up and down auto does the rest. Cheers Dev!
This is the best project management app I have found.  Just one thing I wish for is the ability to link.
This is what I was searching for
Great App
No comparison to the others that I have tried. Easy to figure out. Looking forward to future projects with this app.

It took me a little bit to understand all the features. But now that I have figured everything out, its a nice useful app. My only complaint is the calendar. All works great for standard calendar, butediting and creating new calendars needs to be better
Previously i can do export from mpp data to excel n send or write. My device is LG G3 with lollipop.

Everything is great while displaying gantt with resources inside the app, but when you need to export in PDF (which is an option in the app), the resulting PDF file changes all the resource assignments around! It's presentable and clear, just completely inaccurate! The excel and xml retain original resource integrity - very strange and very annoying. Also, the PNG export is unusable because it cuts most things off, leaving it looking like a partial crop of a screen shot. Paid for the app - disappointed.
Highly functional, wish there were more features. I will probably drop an email to developers as soon as i get time.. I liked it.. Very useful
It has some scope for improvement, however it is brilliant. Congratulations to the developer.
Useful on the go
Still learning. Looks like it will do what I need as soon as I can master app.
Brilliant product with regular enhancements including user suggestions. I use this product daily.
It's good. And getting better. Keep going!!!!
This app is getting better with each update. Great job guys, my projects are becoming more complex, but the app helps to keep everything under controle.

Someone please correct me if I'm wrong, but, after you buy the pro version, if you then want to auto sync to Drive, DropBox, etc., (i.e., no cost to the dev for his own server), you still have to subscribe for $1.50/mo, or $18/yr.  This will quickly add up to one very expensive app!
replyContent: Auto sync is a fully optional feature that is available for a monthly subscription fee of 1$ (paid Project Schedule app) or 1.5$ (free Project Schedule app). Although the synchronized files are stored on a third party storage the synchronisation is propagated to all devices by a dev owned server.

content: Great application
A very useful business tool.  The developer is very responsive and listens to suggestions.  It is definitely worth purchasing.

The application could use more help documentation, but the developer is very quick to respond to questions.  This is the most complete project management software and easiest to use I've found so far for Android.
Unusually powerful for a handheld app

Besides this, the support I received was deficient. I paid for this app and I expect to be given either alternate solutions or at least expectations it would be worked on along. Instead plane answer was "It does not have such feature yet". Aduh!
just an excellent app. using a  note II it was just amazing how fast and easy I updated my project file and send a Pdf to my team. All these in my bed and leastening to music

I tried the free version and then after some feed back from the developer regarding some desired out put I wanted to see/use I paid for it, and I must say I run multiple projects with a large number of people and this is a great business tool. I would like to see the financial and resource side to have some more functionality such as when using past time resource allocation to the schedule but other than that  it's a must have business tool.	I forgot to say I tried the other's and they did not even come class to a real project management program.
Works well

A spreadsheet wouldn't be as 'cute' but would be faster and easier.  Can't find a way to reorganize tasks into positions of  successors, predecessors, parents, and childs.  It can do a couple of these things, but don't change your mind and try to reorganize.  It can't do others.  Can't find useful instructions or troubleshooting on these issues.  It's a nice start for simple projects.
When ur pm is disorganized use this app to keep ur projects and void late night coding.
I'm an engineer with 5 or more projects at a time, the import, notifications and copy to calender make this a very good tool

I can't believe how good this product is. As a self employed builder I project manage some fairly large jobs. I'm permanently attached to my galaxy tab 2 and this software is the best I've installed to date. It does absolutely everything I need, and I can export as PDF to send to customers.  Highly recommended.

1.units for all the Resources are in terms of Rs/hr or Rs/week or day or Month So this units can be only used for Manpower & Machinery. so this app fails When Material units cannot be defined.So units Such as Cum Sft cft Should eigther predefined or an option to define units must be Include.  2. No of units of any resource could not be defined.So here 9t messierably fails with cost calculation &  Resource allocation per task   3.Relations between task Finish to Finish is to be added

Download this App. back in February and still trying to get my head around it. If you have some knowledge of the Microsoft Schedule version, which I don't, maybe this would be of some help. For me the main problem is the on board Help files, a couple of them don't work! and those that do, do not cover all areas, very disappointing. The help desk is non existing! I have written E-mails to this Thorsten guy, to no avail, no answers!
This is what i was looking for, really satisfied except for one thing.  It would be extremely wonderful if there would be task synchronization between devices.
It is a life saver.  :)   Especially with the MPP import,as well as Contacts import and PDF Export. If you use the mpp import there isn't any font problems.  Thanks again & again.  Levent
Except it uses internal storage for no reason. My cheap phone has too little internal storage.
Bug fixes acted on very quickly and suggestions for improvements welcomed and acted on as well. Good app for the price. Not MS Project but very useable.
great PM app with great backup support. Thorsten helped me fix some minor issues.
Please keep up the awesome work

Overall a great project tool. There is a bug with progress indicators when zoomed in, it will move about when part of the task is off screen. Just a visual bug and not major, hopefully the devs will get this fixed soon.

This is the only(!) app out there that allows adding/management of human resources to projects. The others seem to assume all work gets done by ghosts or the program user himself. But the GUI needs some major improvement, and the PDF export functions does not work. Also, please clean up the menu structure on this thing.

I've had this app for some time (one of many dl'd in my search for organization skills). Although it was less used initially, it has more recently become a daily necessity. The dev has made many improvements to the UI, and the app makes it easy to plan my time. Great job!
Great app, works great on my tablet. Able to import and export to MS Project. Perfect for my needs!
Has most features you need and excellent respond from the author! Winning combination...

Its fast, easy to use and visually very effective to communicate all the aspects involved for project management. It has many options, so exploring the context sensitive menus is rewarding. I am already loving it, but am also looking forward to future versions and new features like full resource management, mpp file extension format etc.
The earlier issue has not recurred and am using fluidly. Upgrading to 4 stars. More later as I get through a few completion cycles.
